==English==

===Etymology===
[late Middle English] Historically meant 'expel, drive out'. From Latin ''propellere'', meaning ''pro-'' 'forward' and 
''pellere'' 'to drive'.

===Verb===
'''propel'''

#To cause to [[move]], to [[surge]] [[forward]].

